obo:BFO_0000066  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_441  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The authors use a PKA RII beta knockout mouse to study its role in synaptic plasticity in the visual cortex. It is shown that long term depression (LTD) is abolished in layer V of the visual cortex.\n\nLTD is a postsynaptic process that requires the endocytosis of AMPA receptors (Beattie et al.,Kirkwood and Bear). In the hippocampus, PKA-mediated phosphorylation of GluR1 is required for AMPA trafficking. It has not formally been shown if this is also true in LTD in the visual cortex.. Experimental description: Generation of knock-out and wild-type mice The initial generation of RIIb-/- and AC1/AC8-/-\nmice has been described previously (Brandon et al., 1998; Wong et al., 1999). Here, to\ncontrol for modifiers, mutants were subsequently back-crossed seven or\nmore times into either 129 (129S1/SvImJ; Jackson Laboratories, Bar Har-\nbor, ME) or B6 (C57BL/6; Taconic Farms Inc., Germantown, NY) lines\nfor study." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7620-2704" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1558-1958" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-28" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_441" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

